docs.lead_paragraph: SARANAC LAKE, N.Y., Feb. 1. -- Morris Wood, the champion amateur skater of America, distinguished himself to-day in the ice carnival on Saranac Lake. He started in three races and was winner in all, defeating among others Bellefeuille, the crack skater of Winnipeg. The champion never performed better in his life, and it is believed that he will make some new records before the carnival is over.

docs.lead_paragraph: CLEVELAND, Feb. 2. -- Frank Gotch won the wrestling bout here to-night for the catch-as-catch-can championship. docs.lead_paragraph: BUENOS AYRES, Feb. 6. -- Government troops attacked the rebels, who had fortified themselves at Mendoza, at dawn to-day. Soon afterward the rebel leaders fled to the mountains, whereupon the men surrendered unconditionally. The rebels had sacked the local branch of the National Bank of Buenos Ayres and seized $300,000. Numerous arrests have been made, and the city is now quiet.

JOHNS, N.F., Feb. 13. -- The long-overdue steamer Silvia, from New York and Halifax, arrived here this afternoon after a terrific experience in a blizzard which struck her Wednesday, driving her eighty miles seaward among great ice floes in the Grand Banks. The engines broke down for twenty-four hours in the height of the storm, during which all the passengers and crew labored incessantly at the pumps expecting momentarily that the ship would founder.

headline.main: PASSENGERS AT THE PUMPS.; For Twenty-four Hours Steamer Silvia Was in Danger of Foundering.

docs.lead_paragraph: The bottom fell out of the Erie Railroad yards in Weehawken about noon yesterday into the Pennsylvania Railroad tunnel. There is an immense circular hole in the yards fully 50 feet across and as many deep. Inside are coal cars tilted at a dizzy angle, twisted rails, broken trucks, and one freight car overturned and lying with wheels. The floor of the tunnel is about ninety feet below the track level at this point.

docs.lead_paragraph: MILWAUKEE, Wis., Feb. 23. -- The representatives of the New York Bowling Association won an important victory in the American Bowling Congress to-day. Practically the Congress granted to the New Yorkers all they asked of the National organization, and the general feeling here is that the National tournament of 1907 will not only be held in Greater New York, but the President of the Congress will also be a New York man.

headline.main: NEW YORK BOWLERS GAIN BIG VICTORY; All Demands Practically Granted by Bowling Congress. MAY GET TOURNEY IN 1907 Balls Must Not Weigh More Than Sixteen Pounds -- Home Rule for Local Association.

The occasion was the violent rise in the shares of some of the Southern iron properties. docs.lead_paragraph: A writer who appeals to the multitude must choose his words carefully and be sure always to say exactly what he means. A phrase which would be accepted without question by the few may be as Greek to the many, or, worse, it may be taken to mean more or less than it is intended to convey. Authors whose readers know no literary traditions need not be eloquent, perhaps, but they must always be perspicuous.

docs.lead_paragraph: BERLIN, Feb. 25. -- In the Reichstag to-day, in the course of the discussion of the naval appropriations, Herr Bebel, the Socialist leader, said that if Germany accepted the Naval League's guidance she would, it was estimated, spend $781,250,000 on additions to the fleet. docs.lead_paragraph: ST. PETERSBURG. Feb. 27. -- Maxim Gorky had but a short glimpse of liberty to-day. docs.lead_paragraph: The plans for the new headquarters for the Police Department have been filed with Building Superintendent Hopper by Architects Hoppin and Koen. It is to be a basement and five-story oblong building in classic English style. A gilded dome will rise ninety-two feet above the curb, resembling that of the City Hall.
